Availability Sets ensure that VMs are distributed across multiple hardware groups to reduce downtime.

They protect against:

* Hardware failures
* Planned maintenance

# Real-Life Example:
For example, deploying two VMs in an availability set ensures one remains active during failures.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is critical applications requiring uptime.

Another example is enterprise systems needing redundancy.

Availability sets improve reliability.
